1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Yeah, you wanted to see me?

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Yes, Oscar, come on in.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Close the door, if you would.

4
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Thank you. Thanks so much for talking to me.

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Yeah, sure.

6
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
I'm going in for a procedure today.

7
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Is everything okay?

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Yeah, it's routine. I'm just a little bit scared.

9
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,000
I'm sure everything will be fine.

10
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
What's the procedure, if you don't mind me asking?

11
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
It is a colonoscopy.

12
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Okay.

13
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
In your experience, what should I be expecting

14
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:34,000
in terms of sensation or emotions?

15
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Is there anything I can do to make it more pleasurable

16
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
for me or for Dr. Chandri?

17
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Oh, my God.

18
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,000
My main concern is should I have a safe word?

19
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Yeah.

20
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
I'm sorry.

21
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,000
So, Michael...

22
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Bill Simon from Buffalo.

23
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Thank you.

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Arrow Medical Supplies in West Seneca.

25
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Thanks.

26
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,000
And Angela's still waiting for you to approve

27
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,000
You know what?

28
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
If you're going to keep coming in here with work

29
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
that I need to do, I'm going to need a new monitor.

30
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,000
It's not working.

31
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Hey, Michael.

32
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Yes?

33
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,000
I do want the Buffalo clients under new accounts

34
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,000
to be existing.

35
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,000
I've been doing some of both.

36
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Everybody wants a piece of me.

37
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
So, Michael, how are you handling

38
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,000
the Buffalo transition on your end?

39
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Great. On my end.

40
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
How about your end?

41
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Well, I think we're on the same end, Michael.

42
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Then why did you say your end?

43
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Let me be more specific.

44
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,000
How are you personally handling

45
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,000
the increase in responsibility?

46
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Well, I will tell you, David.

47
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:04,000
I'm either doing the work or I'm not.

48
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
So, are you doing the work?

49
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Maria didn't weep.

50
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Michael, if you need us to help you with anything...

51
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,000
You just let me know, okay?

52
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,000
I'm good.

53
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
I've got a lot of balls in the air.

54
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
If I wanted to be in the business of giving people bad news,

55
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,000
I would have become a coroner or an anchorman.

56
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
But I got into this industry

57
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,000
because I wanted to give people good news.

58
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Like, your paper is on its way.

59
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Yes, we have that in stock.

60
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,000
It's lunchtime.

61
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
So, Michael, you think you can get me a rundown

62
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
on the Buffalo clients by Monday?

63
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,000
You know what? I'll do you one better. Sunday. Sunday night.

64
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Okay. I will get it Monday.

65
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Hold on, big guy.

66
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,000
I'm gonna put it in the mail Sunday night. You'll get it Wednesday.

67
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Okay. Jim, you want to hit the conference room?

68
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Sure.

69
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Okay. Good luck.

70
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,000
All right. This thing. I remember now.

71
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,000
What's this about?

72
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Oh, this is just me and David, if that's okay.

73
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
It's okay. He's gonna want me in.

74
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
No. It's okay, Michael. We got it.

75
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Really? Yeah.

76
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
All right. Do you mind if I sit this out?

77
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
I have so much work to do,

78
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,000
I feel like I'm gonna blow my brains out.

79
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Okay. Go.

80
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
I'm gonna go.

81
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Am I worried that Jim and David are having a meeting without me?

82
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:32,000
No. Because we are the three amigos.

83
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:37,000
And once in a while, one of the amigos will go off to the bathroom

84
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
while the other two have a secret meeting.

85
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Hey, let me escort you to your desk.

86
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
It's just three or four steps, but thank you. Thank you.

87
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
You and Jim are close, huh?

88
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Yeah, I think the pregnancy really brought us together.

89
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Hey. What do you think he and David are talking about?

90
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,000
What are you...

91
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Um, I don't know.

92
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Well, you said good luck to Jim as you walked in.

93
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Did I? Doesn't sound like me. Not very superstitious.

94
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
If you're lying to me right now, Pam,

95
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,000
your baby is gonna come out a liar.

96
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
That's how it works.

97
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
They inherit things through the breast milk.

98
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Please don't talk about my breast milk.

99
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
I just don't want you to lie to me.
